From: "Chia-Lin Kao (AceLan)" <acelan.kao@canonical.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Aug 2022 16:18:45 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: atlantic: fix aq_vec index out of range error
Git-commit: 2ba5e47fb75fbb8fab45f5c1bc8d5c33d8834bd3
Patch-mainline: v6.0-rc1
References: CVE-2022-50066 bsc#1244985

[ Adapted backport. Other patches also fixed the iteration (eg. 8ce84271697a23
  ("net: atlantic: changes for multi-TC support")). Backport changes all for
  loops with cached value aq_vec and replaces with self->aq_vec[i].
]

The final update statement of the for loop exceeds the array range, the
dereference of self->aq_vec[i] is not checked and then leads to the
index out of range error.
Also fixed this kind of coding style in other for loop.

